com.magknight.route.proc.legs

Class LegRF

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.magknight.route.Leg
      • com.magknight.route.proc.legs.LegRF
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LegParser<LegRF>

    public class LegRF
extends Leg
implements LegParser<LegRF>
    RF leg Defines a constant radius turn between two database fixes, lines tangent to the arc and a center fix. For more information. See ARINC database documentation.
    Since:
    5/20/2020
    Author:
    Cian Mc Sweeney

        Initialize a RF leg with specified parameters. (Use accessors to set specific data fields for RF leg).
        Parameters:
        pos - Position of final fix along RF leg arc.
        identifier - Leg identifier.
        bearingFromLast - Undefined for RF leg.
        distanceFromLast - Undefined for RF leg.
        altRestr - Altitude restriction for leg.
        speedRestr - Speed restriction for leg.
        overfly - false for RF leg.
